HEADWORD: Jahvey
<hw>Jahvey</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a name
for the Old Testament God as transliterated from the Hebrew YHVH. See
<er>Jehovah</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Yahweh, Yahwe, Yahveh, Yahve, Wahvey, Jahweh,
Jehovah.</syn>⟦br⟧
